Szymon Szymonowic has recently graduated from St. Mary's College, University of Windsor with a Bachelor of Arts degree in English. His academic background includes two years as a student and three years as an instructor at Niagara College, University of Windsor before his enrollment at St. Mary's College.

He holds a Bachelors Degree of Education with distinction (MEd), a diploma from the Higher Secondary Schools and Colleges of Ontario (HSSCO) and a diploma from the Canadian Institute for International Education (CIIE).

For additional information on this document, please contact:

St. Mary's College, University of Windsor, Suite 535, PO Box 3063, Windsor, ON N8B 4H1

coupled_prompt_600:
State Higher School of Vocational Education in Zamość is a private higher education institution with facilities located in the city of Zamość. It was established on 5 December 1875, and received its current name on 3 February 1926. Its main goal is to provide instruction for Polish citizens who are highly qualified with academic subjects, as well as vocational training and technical knowledge. The mission of the institution is to give students' the opportunity to acquire a professional qualification that will allow them to find success in society, as well as to become active members of their community. This includes the development of individual and collective skills to meet the needs of modern society, as well as their preparation for the demands of employment, career progression and other educational goals.
The University's goal is to develop its students into lifelong learners who have acquired critical reading, writing, and analytical thinking skills, and who have the ability to contribute actively to both national and international societies. Students enrolled at the university may apply for study abroad programs to further their studies and prepare for work. This includes those seeking a job or pursuing advanced study overseas. In addition, the university offers courses in a variety of subjects including, but not limited to: Business; Economics; Information Technology; Law and Society; Mathematics; Natural Sciences and Engineering; Psychology and Behavior; and Public Health and Medicine.
On behalf of Zaraża Polska Śląskiego "ZPA", I invite you to read more about this special institution, and see the wonderful places it has been able to make a difference. We invite you to visit our website and sign up for our newsletter to learn more about what we do.
